track.name: Couldn't Stand The Weather
comments: Stevie Ray at his very best!!  Love it.

Looking at his work, you know that the legacy of the great musicians was transferred into the right hands. His expression in its purest form pleases because most musicians still trying to mix different styles.
Agreed: this must be my favorite SRV track. Smokin'.
Social commentary reminds me of a young Ozzie Osborne. LMAO That geetar pickin' is super duper, too! a little funky, huh?
Intense and smooth at the same time !! WoW !!From the Texas legend.!!
Gran tema. Me fascina Stevie y el blues rock
One of my favorite tracks by Stevie and Double Trouble. Great playing!!
Love his unbelievable skill, and what great tone!! So unique; sweet, yet powerful, never a bad note, just super talent on display!!
You wanna hear some SRV?  Give DRIVIN' SOUTH a listen....he rips it up.  Yes I know Jimmi did a version as well...they both can rip the cover off it.
